  "texts": [
    "Local models may overfit the local datasets, leading to poor generalization on proxy samples outside the local distribution, especially with non-IID data across clients.",
    "To mitigate this issue, our method develops client-side selectors to identify proxy samples that are out of the local distribution (OOD).",
    "This is done through densityratio estimation 48, 49, which calculates the ratio of two probability densities.",
    "Assuming the input data space X is compact, we define U as a uniform distribution with probability density function u(x) over X.",
    "Besides, we denote the probability density function at client k as p k (x)."
  ],
